Definition
-> Move element relative to its original position.
-> Top, left, right, bottom WILL work.
-> Space remains reserved.

Example
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
.box {
 position: relative;
 left: 50px;
 top: 20px;
 background: lightgreen;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="box">Relative Box</div>

</body>
</html>

📌 It shifts from original position but keeps its space.
